main event: A UFO sighting incident occurred in Des Moines, Iowa on 29 June '47 at 16:45 CST. The object observed was described as a 'inverted saucer' with a diameter of 175-225 feet, traveling at a speed of 300 mph.
interesting points: The report mentions multiple redactions, indicating potential classified information.
The sighting involved a group of UFOs, with the first group consisting of 5 objects and then an additional 13.
The color of the UFO was described as 'Light white.'
The document contains references to 'ATIC' (possibly Air Technical Intelligence Center) and an 'Inquiry' form.
The time of the sighting and specific details provide a sense of authenticity to the report.
